ore were often animals or beings which were bound to the mage to spy, be an external source, or even to attack, steal etc.  Here is my proposal both for fun and utility to take the familiar more in this direction:<br>
<br>
Make a spell/AA ability to enable you to control your flappy.  We are talking a modified bind sight utility.  This would make your flappy into something similar to Eye of Tallon.  However I propose that you should not only be able to control movement, but also use it to attack etc. (the flappy already has abilities to riposte dodge etc...and since you are controlling the flappy and not your wizard...no increase in wizzie DPS etc because you cannot cast spells as the familiar...)  Now people are going..wait a minute..you want to give wizards a real pet here....hold on...<br>
What I am proposing that unlike a pet, you would completely control the familiar...losing control of yourself till:<br>
<br>
1: Ability wears off<br>
2: You click off the ability<br>
3: Flappy is killed<br>
<br>
Now according to fantasy... when a Wizard was severed from their familiar, or were done with the familiar, it would leave them drained and weak..having severed a bond.<br>
<br>
What I propose for the penalties:<br>
<br>
1: Ability wears off- Sta is completely drained-stun for 10 secs<br>
2: You click off the ability-Sta is completely drained-stun for 10 secs<br>
3: Flappy is killed-You should have sta completely drained, lost all mana and partial HP-agro transferred to the wizard.<br>
<br>
Now as for the attack abilities of the flappy..just have them have the ability of a typical pet/npc of the level the flappy cons..warrior class would be fine.  Keep it's HP the way it is..and allow it to be buffed before (with firetree's etc) before you take control.<br>
Anyone have any other thoughts?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
